COMPONENT NAME: JKM Informix Consistent
AUTHOR: Oracle
Description: - Journalizing Knowledge Module - This JKM provides consistent journalizing procedures on Informix tables
Restrictions: - When starting the journal on a model, tables no longer in the set are unjournalized, tables missing from the set are journalized. - If the table is already journalized and is present in another model, the current journal data will be lost and the table is transfered to the new journal set. - This Knowledge Module creates triggers on your source tables. Be sure to validate the scalability of your applications before releasing your developments in your production systems.

create table <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("CDC_TABLE_TABLE")%> /* This table is created in the work physical schema set as default for the Data server */ ( CDC_SET_NAME <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR" , "120")%> not null, /* Name of the CDC Set (Sunopsis model code) */ FULL_TABLE_NAME <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "140")%> not null, /* Complete name of the journalized table */ FULL_DATA_VIEW <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "140")%> not null, /* Complete name of the journalizing data view */ RETRIEVE_DATA <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR" , "255", "0" )%>, /* Command to execute to retrieve the journal data (used by the SnpsRetrieveJournalData API) */ REFRESH_ROW_COUNT <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR" , "255", "0" )%>, /* Command to execute to refresh the row count (used by the SnpsRefresh RowCount API) */ primary key (FULL_TABLE_NAME) )

create table <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("CDC_OBJECTS_TABLE")%> /* This table is created in the work physical schema set as default for the Data server */ ( FULL_TABLE_NAME <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "120")%> not null, /* Complete name of the journalized table */ CDC_OBJECT_TYPE <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "35")%> not null, /* Type of the object in the CDC framework */ FULL_OBJECT_NAME <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "210")%> not null, /* Complete name of the object */ DB_OBJECT_TYPE <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "35")%>, /* RDBMS type of the object (ex : TABLE, VIEW, TRIGGER) */ primary key (FULL_TABLE_NAME, CDC_OBJECT_TYPE) )

update <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("CDC_SET_TABLE")%> set RETRIEVE_DATA = NULL, REFRESH_ROW_COUNT = 'update <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("CDC_SUBS_TABLE")%> set CDC_ROW_COUNT=0 where CDC_SUBSCRIBER=''$$SUBSCRIBER_NAME$$'' and CDC_SET_NAME=''<%=odiRef.getObjectName("L", odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_COD_MOD"), "D")%>''' where CDC_SET_NAME = '<%=odiRef.getObjectName("L", odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_COD_MOD"), "D")%>'

insCmd = """ insert into <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("CDC_SUBS_TABLE")%> ( CDC_SET_NAME, CDC_SUBSCRIBER, CDC_REFDATE, MIN_WINDOW_ID, MAX_WINDOW_ID, MAX_WINDOW_ID_DEL, MAX_WINDOW_ID_INS, CDC_ROW_COUNT ) select /* CDC_SET_NAME */ '<%=odiRef.getObjectName("L", odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_COD_MOD"), "D")%>', /* CDC_SUBSCRIBER */ '%s', /* CDC_REFDATE */ current, /* MIN_WINDOW_ID */ CDC.CUR_WINDOW_ID, /* MAX_WINDOW_ID */ -1, /* MAX_WINDOW_ID_DEL */ -1, /* MAX_WINDOW_ID_INS */ -1, /* CDC_ROW_COUNT */ 0 from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("CDC_SET_TABLE")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> CDC where CDC.CDC_SET_NAME = '<%=odiRef.getObjectName("L", odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_COD_MOD"), "D")%>' """
selCmd = """ select count(*) from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("CDC_SUBS_TABLE")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> CDC where CDC.CDC_SET_NAME = '<%=odiRef.getObjectName("L", odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_COD_MOD"), "D")%>' and CDC.CDC_SUBSCRIBER = ? """
# Prepare the statements prepSelStmt = myCon.prepareStatement(selCmd)
# Execute for each subscriber for sbs in lstSbs: prepSelStmt.setString(1, sbs) rs = prepSelStmt.executeQuery() rs.next() nbSubs = rs.getInt(1) if (nbSubs == 0): prepInsStmt = myCon.prepareStatement(insCmd % sbs) nbRows = prepInsStmt.executeUpdate()
prepInsStmt.close() prepSelStmt.close()
# Auto Commit mode the updates #myCon.commit()
